Package projects.spatial.trees

Interface SpatialDictionary

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    KDTree, PRQuadTree
    public interface SpatialDictionary

    SpatialDictionary is an abstraction over any data structure that could be used to allow efficient insertion, deletion and search of KDPoints.

    .

    Minor detail: since SpatialDictionary is an interface, all of its methods are implicitly public, so the explicit scope modifier is not needed in the source.

    YOU SHOULD ***NOT*** EDIT THIS INTERFACE! If you do, you risk not passing our tests!

    See Also:
    KDPoint, BoundedPriorityQueue, SpatialQuerySolver

      • height

        int height()

        Return the height of the SpatialDictionary. The height is defined similarly to AVL trees, as follows:

        1. The height of a null tree (no nodes) is -1 (minus 1).
        2. The height of a tree that consists of a single nodes (a "stub" tree) is 0 (zero).
        3. The height of a tree that consists of four children is the maximum height of its children plus one.
        Returns:
        the height of the subtree rooted at the current node.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Reports whether the SpatialDictionary is empty, that is, it contains 0 (zero) KDPoints.
        Returns:
        true iff count() == 0, false otherwise.
